## root
Usage: harness-kit [options] [command]

AI-friendly repo harness

Options:
  -V, --version              output the version number
  -h, --help                 display help for command

Commands:
  init [options]             scaffold .agents/ skeleton + starter manifest
  sync [options]             generate tool files (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md) from
                             manifest
  doctor [options]           dev-time health check: completeness, drift,
                             freshness, tech debt
  verify [options]           CI gate: run enforceable invariants + contracts +
                             drift; nonzero on failure
  plan-checks [options]      compute which declared checks THIS change should
                             run (impact-driven, executes nothing)
  run-checks [options]       plan + run resolved checks; record evidence;
                             nonzero on failure/unresolved blocking gap
  evidence [options]         show the latest durable run-checks evidence for
                             this worktree/session
  accept-contract [options]  record current contract fingerprint(s) as the
                             accepted baseline (after an intended change)
  install-hooks [options]    install git hooks and/or agent SessionStart + Stop
                             hooks (run-checks + verify gate)
  onboard                    print the erzhe-harness-init skill for an agent to
                             follow (use via npx, always latest)
  check-loop                 print the harness-check-loop skill: the implement
                             -> verify loop for an agent
  help [command]             display help for command

## init
Usage: harness-kit init [options]

scaffold .agents/ skeleton + starter manifest

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --name <name>     project name (default: "my-project")
  --force           overwrite existing manifest (default: false)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## sync
Usage: harness-kit sync [options]

generate tool files (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md) from manifest

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## doctor
Usage: harness-kit doctor [options]

dev-time health check: completeness, drift, freshness, tech debt

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## verify
Usage: harness-kit verify [options]

CI gate: run enforceable invariants + contracts + drift; nonzero on failure

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## plan-checks
Usage: harness-kit plan-checks [options]

compute which declared checks THIS change should run (impact-driven, executes
nothing)

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>      target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --base <ref>          diff base (default: working tree + untracked vs HEAD)
                        (default: "HEAD")
  --profile <checkset>  use a validation.checksets entry instead of per-module
                        checks
  --json                machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help            display help for command

## run-checks
Usage: harness-kit run-checks [options]

plan + run resolved checks; record evidence; nonzero on failure/unresolved
blocking gap

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>      target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --base <ref>          task-start ref; required for manual proof after task
                        changes were committed
  --profile <checkset>  use a validation.checksets entry instead of per-module
                        checks
  --waive <kind>        waive one eligible coverage gap for this exact change
                        fingerprint
  --where <scope>       exact gap scope; required when a kind matches multiple
                        gaps
  --reason <text>       reason recorded with --waive
  --session <token>     validation session token (normally supplied by an agent
                        hook)
  --json                machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help            display help for command

## evidence
Usage: harness-kit evidence [options]

show the latest durable run-checks evidence for this worktree/session

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>   target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --session <token>  specific validation session token
  --json             machine-readable output (default: false)
  -h, --help         display help for command

## accept-contract
Usage: harness-kit accept-contract [options]

record current contract fingerprint(s) as the accepted baseline (after an
intended change)

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --id <id>         only this contract (default: all with a snapshot command)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## install-hooks
Usage: harness-kit install-hooks [options]

install git hooks and/or agent SessionStart + Stop hooks (run-checks + verify
gate)

Options:
  -C, --repo <dir>  target repo dir (default: current directory)
  --git             install git hooks (default when no selector given)
  --stop            install agent SessionStart + Stop hooks (Claude Code /
                    Cursor / Codex)
  --agents <list>   comma list of agent tools for --stop: claude,cursor,codex
                    (default: all)
  --force           overwrite existing hooks (default: false)
  -h, --help        display help for command

## onboard
Usage: harness-kit onboard [options]

print the erzhe-harness-init skill for an agent to follow (use via npx, always
latest)

Options:
  -h, --help  display help for command

## check-loop
Usage: harness-kit check-loop [options]

print the harness-check-loop skill: the implement -> verify loop for an agent

Options:
  -h, --help  display help for command
